For more detial, please reference to Troubleshooting.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
Select the record that the age field value greater than (with using $gt) 10
under the collection, bar, and return only name field and age field with sorting
by ascending order of age field values.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.find(\ {\ age:\ {\ $gt:\ 10\ }\ },\ {\ age:\ "",\ name:\ ""\ }\ ).sort(\ {\ age:\ 1\ }\ )
{
\ \ "name":\ "alice",
\ \ "age":\ 19
}
{
\ \ "name":\ "tom",
\ \ "age":\ 20
}
{
\ \ "name":\ "ben",
\ \ "age":\ 21
}
\f[]
.fi
